&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Interventional Cardiology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a Cardiology Interventional Consultant to support our Primary PCI service at Torbay and South Devon NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a replacement post due to retirement which will start in March 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust provides a 24/7 PPCI, elective PCI, pacing, complex devices, Coronary CT and Cardiac MRI, in addition to standard non-invasive services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We serve a resident population of approximately 286,000 people, plus about 100,000 visitors at any one time during the summer holiday season.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be part of the cardiology team of 4 Cardiology Interventional Consultants and 3 Non-Interventional Consultants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants must be in possession of the essential qualifications for the post, as set out in the person specification by the time interviews take place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Torbay is situated on the coast of South West England and is known as the English Riviera. It is just 20 minutes from Dartmoor National Park, Exeter and the M5, yet surrounded by glorious beaches and idyllic countryside. Local schools are excellent at both the primary and secondary level, with Grammar schools regularly ranked highly in national league tables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information about the post please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Lisa Yung, Consultant Cardiologist and Clinical Lead for Cardiology, 01803 654829 or email lisayung@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
